text: Benjamin Gifford (c. 1688–1713), of Beaminster, Dorset, and Boreham, near Warminster, Wiltshire, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Dorchester from 1710 to June 1713. ==References== Category:1688 births Category:1713 deaths Category:18th-century English people Category:People from Dorset Category:People from Wiltshire Category:Members of the Parliament of Great Britain for English constituencies
